# Question

## you must be able to explain some specifics about this infrastructure:

- What is a server
  ```
  A server is a physical or software device that provived services to other computer they are typically hosted in data centers... this is the operating system
  ```
- What is the role of the domain name
  ```
  Domain name is a readable human format of url which can be translated to an ip address by dns so computers can communicate
  ```
- What type of DNS record www is in www.foobar.com
  ```
  The conical record
  ```
- What is the role of the web server

```
    The webserver recieves request from the user and serves the web-page requested back to the user
```

- What is the role of the application server
  ```
  The application server role is to deal with functionality and bussiness logic requested by the client
  ```
- What is the role of the database
  ```
  the role of the database is to store usefull information that can be accessed by the application server and most importantly Crud operations can be performed
  ```
- What is the server using to communicate with the computer of the user requesting the website
  ```
  it uses TCP/IP
  ```

## You must be able to explain what the issues are with this infrastructure:

- SPOF
  ```
  When one systen fails the whole system is down
  ```
- Downtime when maintenance needed (like deploying new code web server needs to be restarted)
  ```
  When there is an Update to the code base or database a downtime occurs Because there is just one server and when one point is out the whole system is out
  ```
- Cannot scale if too much incoming traffic
  ```
  Whne more users are requesting at the same time the servers get over worked and it causes the server to overload
  ```
